Example of a simple workflow. Everything before the first upcode (@)
is considered a comment/documentation of the workflow and is not
interpreted by gwf.

@target echo
# everything from here to the next @ is considered a shell script.
echo "hello, world!"

@target cat
:input example.gwf
cat example.gwf

@target touch
:output foo
touch foo

@target cat2
:input foo
:output bar
cat foo

@target twoout
:output file1 file2
touch file1
touch file2

@target twoin
:input file1 file2
:output xx
cat file1 file2 > xx

@target catxx
:input xx
cat xx